  "speaker_name": "Julianne",
  "words": "For me as a person who is newer in the youth mental health professional field, I think I've been working in a time that has been perpetuated by change with the pandemic, that we are just experiencing constant change in how the field operates, how we're dealing with mental health. And I think I've been seeing a lot of positive changes in the fact that we're having a lot more open conversations. People are recognizing that mental health is a significant issue, whereas when I was a youth, not too, too long ago that those conversations were not happening. They were not encouraged, they were, it was that fear tactic. Have you tried not worrying about it? Very dismissive. So I've been seeing those changes happening over the years. And in particular, I think the pandemic has been a bit of a speed run of that."
