    "speaker_name": "Julianne",
    "words": "Thinking about this one, it is such a big question, and I think one thing that's coming to mind maybe is finding ways to use our technology to be able to connect across communities, to bring people together more. And we've done a lot over the pandemic to build our technology usage, I think locally. But there's potential with the way technology has grown over the years, that there could be positive ways that it could be used to connect people. But I think a lot of the conversation around technology still is that focus on, Oh, but it could be this bad thing, or, Oh, it is this bad thing. Whereas I'd love to see some shift in conversation too, there are concerns with technology, but there are so many positive things. If we can find a way to look at those, reach those and mitigate some of those risks that people are always concerned about."
