  "words": "As an aside with the technology piece, this has been such a great opportunity these last couple of years to be able to see people have the opportunity to use technology for their benefit of learning more and engaging in different ways. We all can appreciate that we were all headed in this direction anyways to be able to access online learning. But having that speed up of things was incredible in so many ways. Terrible that it came about the way that it did. But I'm glad that we now have been able to see trainings that we would've previously held in one community doing a gatekeeper training in northern Maine. We would have one population that would be at that training, whereas now if we hold something virtually, we can get such a more robust group together. We can have people that are working in schools in southern Maine, northern Maine, eastern Maine, western Maine, and there is so much similarity, but also such different perspectives that come together that way that really allow for some creative thought into how we're navigating all of the things in schools these days. And it's really great to see that different learning styles are being acknowledged in adults, finally. So to be able to see that shorter learning blocks are super effective, so by people having noticed that in adults, that's filtering down to acknowledging that our young people definitely have different learning styles and that it's not a bad thing, that we find what works for an individual and help them be successful with that. That's not making things \"too easy for them\". It's about helping them be successful and be the best version of themselves they can be."
